                <note rend="inline" type="source">823.032/44: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smith</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-29T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 29, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Your 56, March 23, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>What is present Peruvian law regarding those who have taken part in the
                    rebellion? Do you consider law adequate?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
